'''Lena Jordan''' (born 1880/81)<ref name=SMH>{{cite news| url= http://trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/article/14116413| title= Theatre Royal| work=[[Sydney Morning Herald]]| via=[[Trove]]| page=8| date=18 May 1897| accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref> was a [[Russian Empire|Russian]] gymnast, who performed in circuses during the 19th century. In 1897, Jordan was the first recorded person to perform a triple [[somersault]].

==Career==

Jordan started doing gymnastics in the [[Russian Empire]] (now Latvia) in 1892.<ref name=SMH/> She initially worked for the Flying Jordans circus. It was claimed that she performed a triple [[somersault]] during a routine in the US in 1896, although this has not been officially recognised.<ref name=Thomas>{{cite book| url= https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=f1sZBwAAQBAJ&dq=Lena+Jordan+triple+somersault&source=gbs_navlinks_s| title= Victorian Traffic: Identity, Exchange, Performance| last=Thomas| first=Sue| publisher=[[Cambridge Scholars Publishing]]| page=184| date=May 2009| access-date=9 November 2017}}</ref> In May 1897, Jordan, aged 16, became the first recorded person to perform a triple somersault during a routine in Sydney, Australia.<ref name=SMH/><ref name=Thomas/><ref name=HB>{{cite news| url= https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-4145836.html| title= Lena Jordan: Set Record For Daring Trapeze Stunt| work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]| via=[[Highbeam]]| date=15 December 1992| accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite news| url= https://www.nytimes.com/1978/03/19/archives/trapeze-the-quest-for-the-impossible-quadruple-somersault-trapeze.html| title= Trapeze| work=[[New York Times]]| last=Culhane | first=John| date=19 March 1978| accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref><ref name=WP>{{cite news| url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1983/04/02/circus-lives/efae4def-4d07-4372-997f-4e9118ac9fcb/| title= Circus Lives| last=Williams| first=Christian| work=[[Washington Post]]| date=2 April 1983| accessdate=9 November 2017}}</ref> Jordan later joined the [[Barnum & Bailey Circus]], during which time she performed the triple somersault 28 times.<ref name=WP/> For many years, Ernest Clarke was wrongly attributed as performing the first recorded triple somersault. However, he first performed a triple somersault in 1909, 12 years after Jordan. In 1975, the [[Guinness Book of World Records]] acknowledged Jordan as the record holder.<ref name=NYT/><ref name=WP/>

