'''Schweizer Radio: Radio der deutschen und rätoromanischen Schweiz''' ('''SR DRS''') ({{lang-en|Swiss Radio: Radio of the German and Romansh Switzerland}}) (SR GRS) is a company of [[SRG SSR]].
On 1 January 2011, [[Schweizer Fernsehen]] (SF) and Schweizer Radio DRS began the process of merging the two entities into [[Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen]] (SRF). On 16 December 2012, the merger was complete, with SF and SR DSR adopting the SRF name to their television and radio stations.
== Broadcasting == SR DRS own six radio stations, which in [[Linguistic geography of Switzerland|German-speaking]] [[Switzerland]] has a market share of over 60 percent.
